<TEXT>
<P>
 GOING GOING GONE: Vanishing Americana by Susan Jones and Marilyn Nissenson 
(Chronicle: $18.95; 174 pp., paperback original). Jones and Nissenson have 
assembled a wonderful collection of campy old photographs of American pop 
culture; unfortunately, their text often proves less interesting than the 
illustrations. It does seem sad that penmanship, drive-in movies and soda 
fountains are disappearing. But "fan mags" haven't vanished, they've just 
changed their focus, from movie stars to soap opera actors and bubble-gum 
heartthrobs. The Red menace, polio scares and the Motion Picture Production 
Code -- whose departure no one regrets -- seem out of place in a celebration of 
nostalgia. 
</P>
