<BYLINE>
<P>
By Bruce Haring 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 CABLE READY: Apparently being part of the multi-corporate team backing a new 
music video/home shopping cable TV channel isn't enough for Ticketmaster. 
</P>
<P>
 The company -- which has joined EMI Music, PolyGram, Sony Music and the Warner 
Music Group to create a video music channel to challenge MTV -- is preparing to 
launch its own Ticketmaster Channel, devoted to tickets, concert merchandise, 
records and videos. Look for it to be in operation within 90 days. 
</P>
<P>
 Ticketmaster CEO Fred Rosen wouldn't comment on the new channel, but 
acknowledges that he and the company's new owner, Microsoft co-founder Paul 
Allen, "will clearly be investing in and be part of other opportunities that 
are involved in the entertainment highway of the future." Bruce Haring 
</P>
