<HEADLINE>
<P>
FEED A COLD AND POST-QUAKE CRAVINGS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Robin Abcarian really hit the nail on the head with her article on post-quake 
eating habits ("Quake Leaves Shaken Survivors With a Quirk to Chew On," Jan. 
30). 
</P>
<P>
 I was housesitting in Reseda, and after two days of aftershocks, cold cereal 
and total darkness after 5 p.m., I left the house in search of food and pain 
medication for my headache. When I finally found a store that was open, guess 
what I bought? A 10-pack of Kit Kat bars and a large bag of Cheetos. Oh, yes, 
and Excedrin. 
</P>
<P>
 CHARLEE HUTTON 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach 
</P>
</TEXT>
