<HEADLINE>
<P>
A BUSINESSMAN WORTH CHEERING ABOUT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 It was heartening to read your profile of Yvon Chouinard, a man who has been 
able to build a successful business and yet not forget what it's all about ("A 
Man and His Planet," Jan. 28). 
</P>
<P>
 I contrast him with the basically evil and greedy CEOs of large corporations 
-- oil, chemical, mining and timber companies especially -- whose only goals 
are to milk the Earth's resources and the citizens of the world, and who leave 
nothing but poisoned environment. 
</P>
<P>
 These individuals, who earn millions of dollars annually in salaries, bonuses 
and benefits, would much rather spend millions more on public relations and 
buying off politicians than they would on cleaning up the messes they make or 
attempting not to make the messes in the first place. 
</P>
<P>
 I say hooray for Chouinard. 
</P>
<P>
 WALLACE R. DANIELSON 
</P>
<P>
 San Diego 
</P>
</TEXT>
