<HEADLINE>
<P>
DONATING BLOOD IS QUICK AND EASY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 I read "Arming Yourself With the Facts About Donating Blood" (Jan. 26), and I 
want to encourage the community to give the gift of life. 
</P>
<P>
 Donating is easy, and taking 20 minutes out of your day could mean saving a 
life, potentially the life of someone you know. 
</P>
<P>
 Local businesses throughout the country could help in this time of crisis by 
hosting blood drives. I own Designer Donuts in Los Angeles, and we held such an 
event on Jan. 4. All it takes is a call to the American Red Cross, and they 
practically do the rest. 
</P>
<P>
 DENIS HOFFMAN 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
</P>
