<HEADLINE>
<P>
BRIEFLY; EDUCATION: IDE TO SERVE AS VICE PROVOST AT USC 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hollywood Hills resident Richard S. Ide, interim dean of humanities at the USC 
College of Letters, Arts and Sciences, has been named vice provost for 
undergraduate studies. 
</P>
<P>
 He will assume the post in July.Ide will be responsible for the coordination 
of USC's undergraduate education policies. He also will serve as associate dean 
of the university's Leavey Library, where he will assist in the development of 
library-based teaching and learning programs. He will also oversee the 
university's Center for Excellence in Teaching. 
</P>
<P>
 Ide served as associate professor of English from 1984 to 1993, and was 
chairman of the department from 1989 to 1992. He was an assistant professor 
from 1981 to 1984. 
</P>
<P>
 Before joining USC, he served as assistant professor of English at the 
University of Wisconsin at Madison from 1973 to 1981. 
</P>
