<HEADLINE>
<P>
HOSPITAL CHIEF PRAISES STAFF FOR QUAKE RESPONSE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 * The 6.6 earthquake that arrived at 4:31 in the morning on Jan. 17 has 
affected our community and its residents, some severely. Many needed to take 
action to save their lives and those of their families. 
</P>
<P>
 I am a physician in private practice in the San Fernando Valley and serve as 
chief of staff at West Valley Hospital & Health Center in Canoga Park. 
</P>
<P>
 I want to personally and publicly praise the medical staff and hospital staff 
of West Valley Hospital for their heroic services during this disaster. Within 
minutes, the on-duty staff assessed and stabilized the patient population and 
hospital structure and put the triage code into effect. The additional 
physicians, nurses and other hospital staff members arrived within the hour 
following the earthquake to assist with the influx of hundreds of injured 
community residents. 
</P>
<P>
 IRENE FAUST 
</P>
<P>
 Canoga Park 
</P>
