<P>
BROWN'S 10 THREE-POINTERS NOT ENOUGH FOR UC IRVINE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JOHN WEYLER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 UC Irvine hung close to Pacific during much of the first half Saturday night 
and got to within six points with six minutes to play, but the Anteaters gave 
up a couple of easy layups and took a couple of quick shots and lost, 88-79, in 
front of 4,571 at the Spanos Center. 
</P>
<P>
 It was the sixth loss in a row for UC Irvine, which got 36 points and a 
school-record 10 three-point baskets from Chris Brown. 
</P>
<P>
 Brown also tied the Big West Conference record for three-pointers, set by 
Freddie Banks of Nevada Las Vegas in 1987. 
</P>
<P>
 "The effort was pretty good," Irvine Coach Rod Baker said, "but in crucial 
situations, we just didn't make the plays." 
</P>
<P>
 Irvine is 5-13 overall and 2-8 in the conference. Pacific is 14-8, 8-3, half a 
game behind New Mexico State. 
</P>
<P>
 The Anteaters suffered from the same problem that has contributed most heavily 
to their recent woes. Pacific shot 54% from the floor and Irvine made only 39%. 
JOHN WEYLER 
</P>
