<HEADLINE>
<P>
COUNTYWIDE FOCUS: PORT HUENEME; SUSPECTS SOUGHT IN CONDOMINIUM HEISTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Port Hueneme police are searching for suspects in a series of daytime 
burglaries at three condominium complexes. 
</P>
<P>
 Since October, residents have reported about a dozen break-ins at the Harbor 
Lights, Marlboro by the Sea and Sandpiper Village developments.In each case, 
residences were entered after someone kicked in a front door that was shielded 
by a courtyard. 
</P>
<P>
 "They're using their feet," Officer Kenneth Dobbe said. "They just kick the 
door until it breaks the door frame and breaks the locks off." 
</P>
<P>
 The items most frequently stolen have been jewelry, VCRs and televisions. 
</P>
<P>
 Investigators thought that they had the burglaries solved in early January, 
when they recovered stolen property and linked several burglaries to a man who 
was already in jail. But the break-ins have continued and police are searching 
for additional suspects. 
</P>
<P>
 Anyone with information on the burglaries is asked to call Crime Stoppers at 
986-TALK or 385-TALK. If the information leads to criminal charges, the tipster 
may be eligible for a cash reward. 
</P>
<P>
 "If people would just start calling us every time they see something 
suspicious, maybe something would come out of it," Dobbe said. JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
