</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MATTHEW MOSK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A Newbury Park man was in critical condition Saturday evening after he fell 
from the Borchard Road overpass onto the Ventura Freeway and was struck by a 
car, officials said. 
</P>
<P>
 Pushpanden (Peter) Dhillon, 36, of Newbury Park was seen hanging from the 
overpass about 12:20 p.m. Saturday, shortly before he fell into a southbound 
lane, according to the Ventura County Sheriff's Department. 
</P>
<P>
 A motorist told sheriff's deputies she saw Dhillon as he fell and she swerved 
but was unable to avoid hitting him. 
</P>
<P>
 Traffic in the southbound lanes was stopped for about 30 minutes while Dhillon 
was treated by paramedics, officials said. He was then taken to St. 
John's-Pleasant Valley Hospital, where he was listed in critical condition late 
Saturday. 
</P>
<P>
 Dhillon has multiple fractures to his legs, pelvis and ribs, a hospital 
spokeswoman said. 
</P>
<P>
 It was not known if Dhillon intended to jump or if he fell accidentally, a 
sheriff's official said. MATTHEW MOSK 
