<HEADLINE>
<P>
COLLEGE ROUNDUP; PARISI SHARP, POWELL HOT AS TITANS SWEEP ARIZONA 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Mike Parisi threw a three-hit shutout, and Dante Powell had four hits, 
including a home run, and four stolen bases as Cal State Fullerton swept 
Arizona, 9-0 and 6-3, in a nonconference baseball doubleheader Saturday at 
Fullerton. 
</P>
<P>
 Parisi (2-0), a junior right-hander, had a no-hitter through four innings of 
the first game, then gave up singles in the fifth, sixth and eighth innings for 
his first shutout. He struck out seven and walked three. 
</P>
<P>
 Powell stole three bases in the first two innings, helping Fullerton to a 6-0 
lead. Second baseman Jeff Ferguson added three hits, three runs scored and two 
runs batted in. 
</P>
<P>
 In the second game, the Titans (5-1) were tied, 2-2, but scored three runs in 
the fourth. Sal Mancuso had an RBI single, and two more runs scored on an 
Arizona error and wild pitch. 
</P>
<P>
 Powell hit his homer in the seventh. Through six games, he is hitting .483 (14 
for 29), with three homers, 11 RBIs and eight stolen bases. 
</P>
<P>
 Chad Rolish (1-1) gave up three runs and five hits in 5 2/3 innings, striking 
out seven. 
</P>
<P>
 Arizona is 1-4. 
</P>
<P>
 In another nonconference baseball game: 
</P>
<P>
 Point Loma Nazarene 10, Chapman 9 -- Chapman (0-1) scored four times in the 
bottom of the ninth but came up a run short in its season opener at Hart Park 
in Orange. Jason Luciene went three for five and drove in two runs for the 
Panthers. 
</P>
<P>
 In the California Collegiate Wrestling Championships: 
</P>
<P>
 Titans second -- Cal State Fullerton won three individual championships to 
score 71 points, 22 behind champion Fresno State. 
</P>
<P>
 Jeff Maes (126), Christian Holiday (158) and Dwyane Buth (190) were winners 
for the Titans. 
</P>
<P>
 In Big West Conference women's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
 Pacific 80, UC Irvine 62 -- The Anteaters (2-16, 1-9) took 28 more shots than 
Pacific but made four less, shooting just 30% from the field. Jinelle Williams 
led UCI with 21 points and 13 rebounds. 
</P>
<P>
 San Jose State 75, CS Fullerton 66 -- Autumn Hollyfield scored 24 points, 
including six three-pointers, for Cal State Fullerton (2-15, 1-9). San Jose 
State is 11-7, 6-4 
</P>
<P>
 In Golden State Athletic Conference women's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
 Fresno Pacific 79, Concordia 63 -- Freshman Janee Young led Fresno Pacific 
(16-5, 6-0) with 25 points on nine-of-16 shooting. Gitte Mejer led Concordia 
(13-9, 3-3) with 23 points. 
</P>
<P>
 In Golden State Athletic Conference men's basketball: 
</P>
<P>
 Fresno Pacific 74, Concordia 71 -- Vujadin Jovic scored 19 points and had 11 
rebounds, and Craig Martin added 17 points for host Concordia (15-9, 3-4). 
</P>
