<P>
SIX PLAYERS AND THE COACH ARE SICK, SO WASHINGTON STATE WOMEN CANCEL 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Washington State canceled its women's basketball game against Arizona State on 
Saturday night because of illness to six players and Coach Harold Rhodes. 
</P>
<P>
 The Pacific 10 Conference will decide this week if the Sun Devils (2-14, 0-8) 
will be given a victory by forfeit. 
</P>
<P>
 The Cougars (7-10, 2-6) lost, 82-71, to Arizona at Tucson on Thursday night 
and contemplated returning to Pullman, Wash., because the six players still had 
a viral infection. The team traveled to Tempe and hoped rest Friday would help 
the players and Rhodes recover. 
</P>
