<HEADLINE>
<P>
SALSA TO PLAY KEY CONCACAF CUP GAME TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Salsa will attempt to stay alive in play in the CONCACAF Cup at 4 p.m. 
today when it plays Alianza of El Salvador at Cal State Fullerton's Titan 
Stadium. 
</P>
<P>
 The game is the second of a two-game series, and the Salsa needs more than 
just a victory to advance in the Cup, a tournament for soccer league champions 
and runners-up in North and Central America and the Caribbean. 
</P>
<P>
 Alianza won the first game last Saturday in San Salvador, 1-0. Under the 
scoring system, visitors earn two points for each goal and the home team one. 
</P>
<P>
 Salsa victories of 2-1 or 3-2, for example, would still advance Alianza. The 
Salsa would advance by winning, 2-0 or 4-2. 
</P>
<P>
 If the Salsa is ahead by 1-0 or 3-1 at the end of 90 minutes, leaving the 
teams tied in points, they will go immediately to penalty kicks to decide a 
winner. 
</P>
</TEXT>
