<HEADLINE>
<P>
L.A. COUNTY QUAKE DAMAGE: CITY-BY-CITY LOOK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Of the 88 cities in Los Angeles County, more than 50 were touched in some way 
by the Jan. 17 6.6 magnitude earthquake. Attention has been focused on damage 
in the hard-hit San Fernando and Santa Clarita valleys and in parts of south 
and west Los Angeles County. But other cities -- from Alhambra to Whittier -- 
reported damage as well. Here is a city-by-city breakdown: 
</P>
