<HEADLINE>
<P>
SOCCER; ROOSEVELT'S MISSED KICK GIVES GARFIELD A NARROW WIN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ENRIQUE LAVIN, SPECIAL TO THE TIMES 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Roosevelt striker Vicente Mejia missed a second-half penalty kick against 
Garfield on Wednesday, and the Bulldogs held on to a 1-0 win in an Eastern 
League game. 
</P>
<P>
 After a scoreless first half, the Bulldogs opened the second by quickly 
penetrating Roughrider territory. Within two minutes, Julio Cesar Munoz scored 
on a rebound. 
</P>
<P>
 Garfield dominated most of the game, keeping pressure in the midfield and 
escaping the offsides trap to set up plays in front of the goal. The Bulldogs 
nearly scored again when striker Ivan Valente beat Roosevelt goalie Agustin 
Lopez from the right flank and sliced the ball between two defenders toward 
forward Romeo Cordova. But when Cordova slid to put the ball in, he knocked it 
out instead. 
</P>
<P>
 Roosevelt was awarded the penalty kick in the 60th minute when a Bulldog 
touched the ball with his hands in the penalty box.  
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 Bell 8, Locke 0 -- Oswaldo Williams' hat trick gave the Eagles a 5-0 lead 
before the end of first half in a Central League match at Bell. 
</P>
<P>
 The Eagles scored three goals against the Saint defense in the first 15 
minutes of the game. Ernesto Serratos opened the scoring on a breakaway. 
Williams followed with two more tallies, assisted Luis Castillo on the fourth 
and then scored the fifth goal. 
</P>
<P>
 The Eagles have scored 25 goals and have three against them in six games. 
</P>
<P>
 South Gate 3, Fremont 2 -- Riddled with yellow cards and ejections, the Rams 
nearly threw away their victory when the Pathfinders came back from a 3-0 
deficit in the final minutes of Central League action. 
</P>
<P>
 Carlos Osorio scored twice and Eric Salazar tallied once for the Rams, 
seemingly securing their team's third consecutive victory. 
</P>
<P>
 One player from each side was ejected at the end of the first half for 
unsportsmanlike conduct. When the Rams lost another player to accumulated 
yellow cards late in the second half, Fremont made good on its one-man 
advantage. 
</P>
<P>
 With five minutes left, Pathfinder Pablo Gonzalez converted a penalty kick and 
Rene Lemus followed up with another score to close the gap to one goal. Lemus 
almost got the equalizer on the last play of the game when he shot from the 
edge of the penalty box, but the ball hit the crossbar. 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Park 4, Jordan 1 -- Spartan striker Juan Cortez scored one goal in 
each half, both on personal plays, to lead the Bulldogs in an Eastern League 
match. 
</P>
<P>
 Huntington Park forward Jesus Cadenas found the net first on a header from a 
corner kick pass early in the game. Hector Ramos tallied shortly thereafter on 
a rebound from a shot by Mario Mendez for a 2-0 lead. 
</P>
<P>
 Jaime Delgado narrowed the score on header from a corner kick pass, but Cortez 
scored the next two goals to secure the victory. 
</P>
<P>
 Lincoln 3, Marshall 1 -- Carlos Ponce, Melvin Hernandez and Marcelino Salas 
each scored once for a Northern Conference victory. 
</P>
</TEXT>
