<HEADLINE>
<P>
COMMUNITY NEWS: SOUTHEAST: BELL GARDENS; 'A' STUDENTS TO GET LIMO RIDE, DINNER 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JENNIFER OLDHAM 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Bell Gardens Police Department will sponsor a dinner for four straight-A 
students from Bell Gardens Intermediate School at 6 p.m. Wednesday at the 
Gotham Grill, 5811 Firestone Blvd. in South Gate. 
</P>
<P>
 The students, fifth-grader Jennifer Lopez, 10, sixth-grader Vanesa Torres, 11, 
and eighth-grader Heidi Chang, 13, all of Bell Gardens, and seventh-grader 
Yessica Jovel, 12, of Los Angeles were chosen for the honor.Each had a 4.0 
grade-point average. 
</P>
<P>
 Officials held an essay contest to choose the winners because five students in 
each grade qualified for the award, said Bell Gardens DARE Officer Michael So. 
The school includes fifth- through eighth-graders. 
</P>
<P>
 Students were asked to choose from three questions -- what they would do to 
improve their school, whom they trusted the most and why, or what they would 
tell their children. 
</P>
<P>
 So, who coordinates the DARE program at Bell Gardens Intermediate, created the 
recognition dinner "to provide an incentive for kids to achieve their potential 
in school."  
</P>
<P>
 The honorees, scheduled to arrive at the dinner in a limousine with their 
parents, will be asked to give speeches during the festivities for police, 
parents and Bell Gardens city officials. JENNIFER OLDHAM 
</P>
